{"word":"ἄπαυστος","slug":"ἄπαυστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄπαυστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>παύομαι</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>unceasing, never-ending</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>not to be stopped</i> or <i>assuaged, insatiable</i>, <el>δίψα</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>never ceasing from</i>, <el>γόων</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}